$ link /ENTRY

The `/ENTRY` option specifies the symbol of the start address for an exe or a → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/DLL[dll].

This entry point is expected to have *stdcall* → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/calling-convention[calling convention].

{ Default entry points

table { lll

  → Windows/development/Visual-Studio/link/subsystem[`/SUBSYSTEM:CONSOLE`] ☰ `mainCRTStartup` or `wmainCRTStartup`       ☰ → Windows/development/CRT/source/crt0_c[`crt0.c`]
  → Windows/development/Visual-Studio/link/subsystem[`/SUBSYSTEM:WINDOWS`] ☰ `WinMainCRTStartup` or `wWinMainCRTStartup` ☰ → Windows/development/CRT/source/wincrt0_c[`wincrt0.c`]
  `/DLL`                                                                   ☰ `_DllMainCRTStartup`                        ☰ → Windows/development/CRT/source/dllcrt0_c[`dllcrt0.c`]

table }

}
